    â””â”€â”€ metacognitive â”€â”€â–¶ seja-brief / seja-chronicler
```

### 2.2 Direct routing (bypass triage)

- **Urgent/blocked**: route directly to `@seja-oracle` or `@seja-council`
- **Metacognitive work** (docs, briefs, session summaries): route directly to `@seja-docs`, `@seja-brief`
- **Semiotic evaluation**: route directly to `@seja-semiotic`
- **Explicit agent mention**: `@agent-name` bypasses triage entirely

### 2.3 Triage classification schema

| Field | Values |
|-------|--------|
| Urgency | `immediate`, `this-session`, `next-session`, `backlog` |
| Domain | `strategy`, `architecture`, `planning`, `implementation`, `quality`, `research`, `documentation`, `operations`, `metacognitive`, `semiotic` |

## 3. LIFECYCLE FSM

### 3.1 States

```
setup â†’ design â†’ research â†’ plan â†’ implement â†’ check â†’ document â†’ reflect â†’ design (cycle)
```

### 3.2 Forward transitions with guards

| From | To | Guard | Hard block |
|------|----|-------|------------|
| setup | design | constitution_not_empty | YES |
| design | research | design_intent_defined | YES |
| research | plan | research_recommendation_clear | Advisory |
| plan | implement | plan_approved | YES |
| implement | check | all_steps_done | YES |
| check | document | all_checks_passed | YES |
| document | reflect | documentation_generated | Advisory |
| reflect | design | (none) | â€” |

### 3.3 Reverse transitions (C8)

| From | To | Guard | Hard block |
|------|----|-------|------------|
| implement | design | reason_provided | YES |
| implement | research | reason_provided | YES |
| plan | design | reason_provided | YES |

### 3.4 Forced transitions

Any state â†’ any state with `force=true`. Always recorded in `lifecycle_history` with timestamp and reason.

### 3.5 Sandbox branch

```
implement â”€â”€â–¶ sandbox (experimentation) â”€â”€â–¶ implement (merge or discard)
                                              â””â”€â”€â–¶ design/research (prototype feedback)
```

## 4. AXIOMS (NON-OVERRIDABLE)

These axioms apply to ALL agents in ALL projects. Local AGENTS.md may add stricter constraints but never relax these.

### 4.1 Git axioms
- **No push**: agent never executes `git push` to any remote
- **No merge to main without check**: agent never merges experiments or branches to main without explicit `@seja-check` approval
- **Auto-commit after each step** (W5): `git add -A && git commit -m "step N: [title]"` â€” never accumulate uncommitted changes

### 4.2 Decision axioms
- **No delete**: agent never deletes decision records (`seja.decisions.delete()` does not exist)
- **No edit**: agent never modifies existing decision records
- **No constitution write**: agent never writes to constitution (`seja.constitution.write()` does not exist)
- **No brief mutation**: agent never edits or deletes briefs (`seja.briefs.edit()` does not exist)

### 4.3 Implementation axioms
- **No implement without approved plan**: never execute implementation steps without `plan_id` where status = `approved`
- **Checker between steps** (D16): step N+1 does not start without checker completion on step N (unless `checker: false` in plan)
- **No read secrets**: agent never reads `/run/secrets/` â€” this is enforced at permission layer (A2)
- **No push experiment branches**: never push experiment branches to remote (invariant 27)

### 4.4 Invocation axioms
- **Always log briefs**: every agent invocation must call `seja.briefs.log_started()` and `seja.briefs.log_done()`
- **Always record telemetry**: every invocation must call `seja.telemetry.record_invocation()`
- **Always present rationale**: every recommendation must include reasoning
- **Always show alternatives**: every recommendation must show "recommended when" and "not recommended when"

### 4.5 Security axioms
- **Security wins by default**: security overrides performance and convenience
- **Accessibility non-negotiable**: never trade accessibility against visual design or performance
- **Document trade-offs**: when deferring a perspective, record the rationale

